   JWT's First Nuprin Ad
                                                                                                       

   A new TV commercial for Bristol-Myers Squibb's Nuprin
brand -- one that asks consumers to "Tell Nuprin Where it
Hurts" -- will begin airing tonight.
   The ad is the first from J. Walter Thompson, the New York
shop named just last month to replace Grey Advertising as
agency for the $30 million account.
   Bristol-Myers tapped Thompson, a unit of WPP Group,
following a review in which it asked a few agencies for ideas
on how to fire up sales of Nuprin, an ibuprofen pain reliever
that has been a distant competitor to market leader Advil.
   The Thompson spots show adults as victim to various kinds
of pain, like head and back, and make the pitch that Nuprin
is the answer to all of them. Pain-plagued consumers shown
jogging and driving cars are the spots' stars.
   The spots also feature a neon "body map" showing how
Nuprin goes after pain. And reminiscent of Grey's old
campaign showing the "little, yellow, different" pills as the
only color in otherwise black-and-white spots, the new ads
show Nuprin pills glowing in the "body's" neon hand.
