   Ad Notes. . . .
                                                                                                       

   FOOTE CONE: Foote, Cone &amp; Belding Communications, Chicago,
reported second-quarter net income rose 9.4% to $7.4 million,
or 73 cents a share, from $6.8 million, or 67 cents a share,
in last year's second quarter. Revenue rose 6.4% to $84.7
million from $79.6 million a year earlier.
                                                                                                       

   GREY: Grey Advertising, New York, said second-quarter net
rose 4.5% to $5.1 million, or $3.96 a share, from $4.9
million, or $3.73 a share, in the year-earlier period.
Second-quarter revenue rose 10% to $117.6 million from $106.8
million.
                                                                                                       

   NESCAFE ADS: Nescafe today begins airing ads for its new
Brazilian Supreme and Colombian Gold instant coffees,
positioning the varieties as the choice of those "who have a
passion for coffee." In one ad, a Latin beat rumbles as a
handsome young couple meets for a cup of morning brew. "South
Americans have a passion for life," an announcer says. "And
the coffee they feel most passionate about is Nescafe." The
ads were created by McCann-Erickson's New York office.
